{
  "texts": [
    "As noted by Engel et al. (2020a), the neural source-filter model introduced by Wang et al. (2019b) can be considered a form of waveshaping synthesiser.",
    "This family of models, based on the classical source-filter model, replaces the linear synthesis filter H(z) with a neural network f θ, which takes a source signal x [n] as input, and also accepts a conditioning signal z [n] which alters its response.",
    "Due to the nonlinearity of f θ, we can interpret its behaviour through the lens of waveshaping-that is, it is able to introduce new frequency components to the signal.",
    "Thus, for a purely harmonic source signal, a harmonic output will be generated, excluding the effects of aliasing.",
    "The proposed neural filter block follows a similar architecture to a non-autoregressive WaveNet (van den Oord et al., 2016), featuring dilated convolutions, gated activations, and residual connections."
  ]
}